@article{ISI:000370456500007,
	Abstract = {{Cyber-Physical Systems (CPSs) represent a new generation of digital
   systems, where cyber entities and physical devices cooperate towards a
   set of common goals. The research presented in this paper aims to
   contribute to the development of CPSs by proposing: (1) an analysis
   methodology to model the CPS's behavior in terms of dependability; and
   (2) a CPS architecture with dependability facilities applicable in
   environmental monitoring, based on the Wireless Sensor Network,
   multi-agent and cloud computing technologies. The proposed methodology
   combines a primary dependability analysis technique with the
   representation of knowledge in order to support the development of CPSs
