@article{ISI:000334161000004,
	Abstract = {{The advances in wireless communication technologies, vehicular networks
   and cloud computing boost a growing interest in the design, development
   and deployment of Vehicular Cyber-Physical Systems (VCPS) for some
   emerging applications, which leads to an increasing demand on connecting
   Mobile Cloud Computing (MCC) users to VCPS for accessing the richer
   applications and services. In this paper, we first identify the key
   requirements of designing an efficient and flexible architecture for
   integrating MCC and VCPS. Based on the requirements, we design a VCPS
   and MCC Integration Architecture (VCMIA), which provides mobile services
   for potential users such as drivers and passengers to access mobile
   traffic cloud. Then, we ana- lyze two crucial cloud-supported
   components: GIS with traffic-aware capability and cloud-supported
